```sql
-- models/intermediate/int_deduped_returns.sql
-- Deduplicate returns to one approved return per item
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        return_id,
        item_id,
        return_date,
        reason,
        status,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY item_id
            ORDER BY status DESC, return_date ASC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_returns') }}
)
SELECT
    return_id,
    item_id,
    return_date,
    reason,
    status
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

```sql
-- models/intermediate/int_items_with_returns.sql
-- Join items with deduped returns to identify returned items
WITH items AS (
    SELECT
        oi.item_id,
        oi.order_id,
        oi.product_id,
        oi.quantity
    FROM {{ ref('stg_order_items') }} oi
)
SELECT
    i.item_id,
    i.order_id,
    i.product_id,
    i.quantity,
    CASE WHEN r.return_id IS NOT NULL THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS is_returned
FROM items i
LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_deduped_returns') }} r
    ON r.item_id = i.item_id
```

```sql
FROM items_returns ir
```

-- models/mart/fct_return_rates_by_category.sql
-- Calculate product return rates by category
WITH item_category_data AS (
    SELECT
        ic.item_id,
        ic.category_id,
        ic.quantity,
        ic.is_returned
    FROM {{ ref('int_items_with_categories') }} ic
)
SELECT
    COALESCE(c.name, '(unknown)') AS category_name,
    SUM(icd.quantity) AS total_items_sold,
    SUM(CASE WHEN icd.is_returned = 1 THEN icd.quantity ELSE 0 END) AS total_items_returned,
    ROUND(
        SUM(CASE WHEN icd.is_returned = 1 THEN icd.quantity ELSE 0 END)::NUMERIC /
        NULLIF(SUM(icd.quantity), 0),
        4
    ) AS return_rate
FROM item_category_data icd
LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_categories') }} c
    ON c.category_id = icd.category_id
GROUP BY
    COALESCE(c.name, '(unknown)')
ORDER BY
    return_rate DESC
